io.github.hhromic.uimr.as

Class Collection

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.hhromic.uimr.as.Collection

  • public class Collection
extends Object

    This class represents an Activity Streams Objects Collection.

    This class is a direct representation of the JSON Serialization provided from the Activity Streams website in http://activitystrea.ms/specs/json/1.0/#collection.

    A Collection is a generic list of ASObjects of any object type. The ASObject.objectType of each item in the collection MAY be omitted if the type of object can be established through context. The collection is used primarily as the root of an Activity Streams document, but can be used as the value of extension properties in a variety of situations.

    A valid Collection MUST contain at least the url or items properties.

    Since:
    4.0
    Author:
    Hugo Hromic

    • Field Detail

      • totalItems

        protected Integer totalItems

        Non-negative integer specifying the total number of activities within the stream. The Stream serialization MAY contain a totalItems property.

      • items

        protected ASObject[] items

        An array containing a listing of ASObjects of any object type. If used in combination with the url property, the items array can be used to provide a subset of the ASObjects that may be found in the resource identified by the url.

      • url

        protected String url

        An IRI [RFC3987] referencing a document containing the full listing of objects in the collection.
